'''Ana Julia Bridges'''<ref>{{cite web | title = Faculty directory: Ana Julia Bridges | url = http://directory.uark.edu/people/abridges | website = uark.edu | publisher = [[University of Arkansas]] |accessdate= December 27, 2015 }}</ref> is an assistant professor at the department of psychological science, [[University of Arkansas]],<ref>{{cite web | title = Ana Bridges | url = http://psyc.uark.edu/3512.php | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150922200717/http://psyc.uark.edu/3512.php | publisher = Department of Psychological Science, [[J. William Fulbright College of Arts and Sciences]], [[University of Arkansas]] | archive-date = September 22, 2015 | accessdate = December 27, 2015 }}</ref> and one of the chief editors of the journal ''[[Sexualization, Media, and Society]]''.<ref>{{cite web | title = Editorial board: Sexualization, Media, and Society | url = https://uk.sagepub.com/en-gb/eur/sexualization-media-society/journal202355#editorial-board | publisher = [[Sage Publications|Sage]] | accessdate = December 27, 2015| date = 2015-10-27 }}</ref>

== Education ==
Bridges received her PhD in clinical psychology from the [[University of Rhode Island]] in 2007.<ref>{{citation | last1 = Sigal | first1 = Janet A. | last2 = Denmark | first2 = Florence L. | author-link2 = Florence Denmark | contribution = About the editors and contributors | editor-last1 = Sigal | editor-first1 = Janet A. | editor-last2 = Denmark | editor-first2 = Florence L. | editor-link2 = Florence Denmark | title = Violence against girls and women: international perspectives | page = 263 | publisher = Praeger, An Imprint of ABC-CLIO, LLC | location = Santa Barbara, California | year = 2013 | isbn = 9781440803352 | ref = harv | postscript = .}}</ref>

